WEBVTT

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:06.440
Just go inside first.
You'll see soon enough.

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:11.320
Ugh, I'm not going in. I already told you
I'm not coming to Ameena's house.

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.600
I'm tired of all this drama.

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:17.440
I'm not bringing you here
to pick a fight with her. Trust me.

00:00:27.800 --> 00:00:29.760
Such a gentleman.

00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:33.600
Auntie.

00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:38.880
It's me, Warat. Grandma Wanee's grandson.

00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:42.440
Oh, I remember now. Mr. Warat. Wow.

00:00:42.520 --> 00:00:44.920
You've grown into
such a handsome young man. Hello.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:46.880
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:00:46.960 --> 00:00:48.760
Oh, hello.

00:00:49.280 --> 00:00:51.120
Uh, Madam isn't here.

00:00:51.200 --> 00:00:53.160
She's been abroad for several days.

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:58.400
Ms. Ameena isn't here either. She stays
at her condo and rarely comes back.

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:01.960
Okay. Then please
pass these fruits to the family for me.

00:01:02.040 --> 00:01:02.880
Sure.

00:01:02.960 --> 00:01:05.800
I'll have my staff carry them inside.

00:01:05.880 --> 00:01:06.960
Auntie, come on.

00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:08.600
-Please, come in.
-Take us inside. It's hot.

00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:13.080
Such a gentleman.

00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:41.800
Hello, it's Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

00:03:41.880 --> 00:03:44.720
I'd like to ask about a child there.

00:03:44.800 --> 00:03:48.120
I made a donation a long time ago.

00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:50.360
I just want to know

00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:53.040
how she's doing now,

00:03:53.120 --> 00:03:55.600
what grade she is in?

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:59.040
Sure. Thank you so much
for caring about the children.

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:01.360
An officer will call you back.

00:04:01.440 --> 00:04:04.680
May I ask what the child's name is?

00:04:07.320 --> 00:04:08.600
You don't remember?

00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:14.600
Then I'm afraid not. We cannot provide
the children's names. I'm sorry.

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:17.120
Really?

00:04:17.880 --> 00:04:20.839
What if the name is…

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:22.560
What's the name again?

00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:23.920
It's…

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:25.720
Who are you talking to, Anong?

00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:29.960
If so, may I have your name
and a contact number?

00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:31.280
I need to go now.

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:32.280
Hello?

00:04:32.960 --> 00:04:34.840
Hello? Hello?

00:04:36.760 --> 00:04:38.040
Arnon.

00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:39.640
Did you hear the conversation?

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:42.680
That woman on the phone sounded strange.

00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:45.960
Yeah, I felt something was off too.

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:50.480
I've got goosebumps. What is this?

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:53.240
Could it be that
the people who hurt my dad

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:55.840
know we've started
investigating Kluay's case again?

00:04:57.840 --> 00:04:59.880
Dad was side-swiped twice,

00:05:01.360 --> 00:05:03.280
and then finally hit by a car and…

00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:10.000
Hey, don't jump to conclusions yet.
It might not be that serious, alright?

00:05:10.080 --> 00:05:14.040
Does this phone show the caller's number?

00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:23.200
It's okay. I'll contact the operator

00:05:23.280 --> 00:05:25.680
and check the number.

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:28.600
Let's go.

00:05:31.600 --> 00:05:34.520
Did she tell you her name?

00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:39.440
No, but I heard someone nearby call her

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:41.400
Nong.

00:05:42.360 --> 00:05:43.680
-Nong?
-Yeah.

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:45.480
Nonglak? Nongnuch?

00:05:46.400 --> 00:05:48.560
There are so many Nongs.

00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:51.360
Let's just try to remember for now
before we forget.

00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:55.360
Arnon, should we tell Mama Toi about this?

00:05:56.320 --> 00:05:59.560
I don't think we should.
You're already this shaken.

00:06:00.080 --> 00:06:02.680
If Mama Toi hears about it,
it'll be worse.

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.640
But what if that Nong woman

00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:08.760
calls back when we're not here
and Mom answers?

00:06:09.560 --> 00:06:11.080
I'll find a way to tell her,

00:06:12.440 --> 00:06:14.680
in a way that won't shock her too much.

00:06:17.320 --> 00:06:20.920
What should we do? Let's go.

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:28.480
Please have a seat. Have some water.

00:06:28.560 --> 00:06:31.560
I'll have someone
take the fruit basket inside.

00:06:31.640 --> 00:06:36.400
Wait, auntie.
Why don't you sit and chat with us first?

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:38.040
Is there something wrong?

00:06:40.920 --> 00:06:44.320
Well, I haven't been here in a long time.

00:06:44.920 --> 00:06:47.680
I just wanted to talk to you,

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:51.000
just to catch up with you. Have a seat.

00:06:52.360 --> 00:06:55.600
I just moved into
the Vanich house not long ago.

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.000
I don't really know
anyone around here yet.

00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:08.360
Auntie. Actually, the two of us

00:07:09.840 --> 00:07:11.200
are getting married.

00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:21.560
Babe,

00:07:21.640 --> 00:07:24.200
if you're ever lonely at home,

00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:27.920
you can come chat with auntie.
She's very kind. Okay?

00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:32.440
Is that alright?

00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:34.600
Of course.

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:40.680
The bride-to-be is so beautiful.

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:43.200
Congratulations, Mr. Warat.

00:07:43.280 --> 00:07:45.000
Right? She's beautiful, isn't she?

00:07:45.080 --> 00:07:47.760
If my parents were still alive,

00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:49.320
they'd be

00:07:49.400 --> 00:07:52.600
as happy as you are to see me
with such a beautiful girlfriend.

00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:54.760
-Right?
-Yes.

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:59.960
Mr. Wichan and Ms. Praewilai…

00:08:00.040 --> 00:08:05.120
So auntie,
you knew my family well, didn't you?

00:08:05.200 --> 00:08:08.120
Back then, yes.
But now I hardly know anyone.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:10.440
The old house staff

00:08:10.520 --> 00:08:13.160
have all gone.

00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:15.120
What about Pong and Soi?

00:08:16.440 --> 00:08:18.520
Were you close to them?

00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:20.120
Those two?

00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:22.080
They came later.

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:24.880
They were Ms. Ampha's people.

00:08:25.640 --> 00:08:28.280
Ms. Ampha? My dad's wife?

00:08:29.120 --> 00:08:32.880
Oh, you still remember her?

00:08:32.960 --> 00:08:35.320
Of course I remember.

00:08:35.400 --> 00:08:38.520
I… I remember.

00:08:38.600 --> 00:08:42.960
Ms. Ampha took care of you for a while.

00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:47.720
Back then, they often came over
and hung out at Ms. Ameena's house.

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:51.000
I heard that Ms. Ampha

00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.960
disappeared along with Pong and Soi.

00:08:54.640 --> 00:08:56.320
Yes. I heard that too.

00:08:56.400 --> 00:08:59.120
All three vanished without a trace.

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:03.880
Your family kept it very quiet.

00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:06.920
Even my nephew, who worked for Pong,

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:08.920
didn't know what happened.

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:11.720
Do you know where they went?

00:09:16.160 --> 00:09:18.680
I think Ms. Ameena's car just drove in.

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:25.480
Auntie, please don't tell anyone

00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:29.000
that I asked
about Pong, Soi, and Ms. Ampha.

00:09:29.080 --> 00:09:30.760
Oh, of course.

00:09:33.880 --> 00:09:34.720
Let's go.

00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:40.160
Goodbye.

00:09:44.360 --> 00:09:47.160
Why are you here? Did you come
all the way here to pick a fight?

00:09:49.840 --> 00:09:51.480
Good. Since you know, shall we start?

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:52.440
Hey.

00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:59.880
So you're not going to tell me
who you were talking to?

00:10:01.240 --> 00:10:04.520
You're seeing this, right? I'm busy now.

00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:08.120
Then stop. I'm not hungry anymore.
I'm not eating anything.

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:16.040
You've been acting strange lately.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:19.400
Yesterday, I called for you for so long.

00:10:19.480 --> 00:10:23.480
And you said you went outside,
or went for a walk.

00:10:24.480 --> 00:10:29.120
I've been feeling bloated lately,
like early menopause.

00:10:29.200 --> 00:10:32.160
So I went for a walk to digest dinner.

00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:34.400
And earlier?

00:10:34.480 --> 00:10:36.280
Why did you go over there to talk?

00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:39.440
Why not talk here?
There's a dining table, a sofa.

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:42.000
Who were you talking to?

00:10:42.080 --> 00:10:45.720
Or did you not want me to hear
what you were saying?

00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:01.240
Hello, it's Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:04.160
Are you contacting
the registry department?

00:11:07.360 --> 00:11:09.080
It's an orphanage.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.400
I wanted to make merit for your birthday.

00:11:16.160 --> 00:11:17.720
Come on.

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:23.400
Nong, I'm old already.
Don't do birthday surprises like that.

00:11:23.480 --> 00:11:25.960
Don't do this again, alright?

00:11:28.760 --> 00:11:30.200
Alright, alright.

00:11:30.280 --> 00:11:34.880
What else is on the menu besides this?
Go get it and let me see.

00:11:34.960 --> 00:11:37.680
Sure, please wait a moment.

00:11:48.840 --> 00:11:49.800
Baan Saeng Wan Mai.

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:54.600
BAAN SAENG WAN MAI

00:11:55.240 --> 00:11:57.160
Hey, stop right there.

00:11:57.240 --> 00:11:59.160
Come back and talk this through, Kluay.

00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:02.400
You sent your sister to blackmail me.

00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:04.280
What do you want now?

00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:07.240
Are you going to tell my parents?

00:12:07.320 --> 00:12:10.040
Isn't this going too far, Kluay?

00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:13.760
-Mr. Warat, what am I supposed to say?
-I don't know.

00:12:19.640 --> 00:12:24.360
Yes, I'll tell your parents everything,
about all your awful behavior.

00:12:24.440 --> 00:12:27.600
I'll tell them everything,
from high school to university.

00:12:27.680 --> 00:12:31.320
That homework notebook
you soaked in the toilet.

00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:35.200
And also the thesis project model
that I was about to submit.

00:12:35.280 --> 00:12:38.480
The one you dropped
your stuff on and said,

00:12:38.560 --> 00:12:41.000
"Oh, I didn't mean to, Kluay."
Who would believe that?

00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:42.880
And one more thing.

00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:45.520
My school uniform that you
threw in the trash,

00:12:45.600 --> 00:12:48.000
so I had to wear
my swimsuit cover-up home.

00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:49.440
How could you do that, Ameena?!

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:53.480
And the latest thing,
you hired people to slap me.

00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.600
What is wrong with you?!

00:12:55.680 --> 00:12:59.440
I can't take it anymore, Ameena. I can't!

00:12:59.520 --> 00:13:00.760
I can't either!

00:13:10.840 --> 00:13:11.960
Feel relieved now?

00:13:13.800 --> 00:13:15.480
Relieved? Are you crazy?

00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:17.320
I've never acted like this before.

00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:20.960
It's because of you
that I had to play the crazy girl.

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:25.880
Good. At least you were being yourself.

00:13:25.960 --> 00:13:27.760
See? Ameena went pale.

00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:32.680
Mr. Warat, Ameena
would never really go pale.

00:13:32.760 --> 00:13:34.960
You heard everything I've been through.

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:38.280
I'm telling you,
after this, I'm dead for sure.

00:13:38.960 --> 00:13:41.880
Come on. At least she doesn't know

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:43.720
we went there
to investigate about Ms. Ampha.

00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:48.720
True. If Ameena hadn't come back so fast,

00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:52.960
we would already know
where the maid's nephew works.

00:13:53.560 --> 00:13:56.040
It's not that hard. We've got Arnon.

00:13:57.200 --> 00:14:00.720
Why? With Mr. Arnon,
will we magically know more?

00:14:00.800 --> 00:14:03.160
Is he Abdul or something?

00:14:04.880 --> 00:14:07.800
Abdul? Who's Abdul?

00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:12.640
You know, Abdul, ask anything and
he answers. You've never heard of that?

00:14:16.080 --> 00:14:17.200
What are you even talking about?

00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:20.200
Talking to
a spoiled rich kid is exhausting.

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:22.360
What?

00:14:25.880 --> 00:14:28.920
So you're going to have Mr. Arnon

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:32.960
investigate which company
the maid's nephew works at?

00:14:34.120 --> 00:14:38.680
That's child's play for Arnon's team.

00:14:40.840 --> 00:14:44.320
And after we find out
the company name, then what?

00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:46.720
It still feels roundabout.

00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:51.080
You say that like we have another option.

00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:57.920
Actually, we do.

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:01.160
But it depends on whether you're willing.

00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:03.560
What?

00:15:05.440 --> 00:15:08.200
You have to make peace with Sin.

00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:21.040
No way.

00:15:21.640 --> 00:15:24.040
I haven't even finished speaking
and you already refused.

00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:32.200
Why? Why cancel the internal meeting?

00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:34.920
For a major project like this,
you can't just skip steps

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.680
and go straight
to the shareholders' board.

00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:40.280
You can't do that, Sin.

00:15:40.360 --> 00:15:42.880
I know, Mom.

00:15:43.600 --> 00:15:44.760
But if

00:15:46.040 --> 00:15:49.440
Mr. Warat refuses to sign off
on the hotel comments,

00:15:49.520 --> 00:15:51.280
there's nothing I can do.

00:15:52.040 --> 00:15:55.040
Why do you have to get in everyone's way,

00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:58.240
playing childish games, Warat?

00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:02.920
Mr. Warat probably thinks

00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:05.440
I'm trying to take over
the Vanich business.

00:16:06.040 --> 00:16:10.920
As if it were that easy. Ugh, Rat.

00:16:11.920 --> 00:16:16.240
Please don't be upset with me
for meddling in your family matters.

00:16:16.840 --> 00:16:18.560
What are you saying?

00:16:18.640 --> 00:16:22.920
I've taken care of you
as if you were family.

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:25.560
You're like a son to me too.

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:29.600
Thank you so much, Mom. Well, Mom.

00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:34.000
I'd like you to transfer
the majority shares to Mr. Warat.

00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:40.240
That way, he'll stop thinking
I'm after something from you.

00:16:43.080 --> 00:16:47.560
Well… If Mr. Warat
holds the majority shares,

00:16:48.520 --> 00:16:51.960
he'll work wholeheartedly for you,
with no excuses.

00:16:54.080 --> 00:16:55.720
It's worth considering.

00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:58.240
To be honest,

00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:01.040
I'll benefit too.

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.760
If Mr. Warat holds the majority shares,
I can work to my full potential.

00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:09.200
Vanich will grow the way you want.

00:17:16.119 --> 00:17:18.800
Then I'll excuse myself.

00:17:29.440 --> 00:17:31.680
I've decided.

00:17:32.320 --> 00:17:34.760
I won't transfer the shares to Warat.

00:17:34.840 --> 00:17:37.200
I'll draft a new will instead.

00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:40.680
Right now, ma'am?

00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:42.720
If not now, then when?

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:45.840
Since Wichan passed away,

00:17:45.920 --> 00:17:48.840
I haven't amended the will at all.

00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:53.480
All the assets are still
entirely under Wichan's name.

00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:56.720
With the utmost respect,

00:17:56.800 --> 00:17:59.920
everything would go to Mr. Warat anyway

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.720
as Mr. Wichan's heir.

00:18:03.240 --> 00:18:04.400
Is that what you think?

00:18:06.840 --> 00:18:11.440
What if someone starts digging into it?

00:18:14.200 --> 00:18:18.960
Ridiculous. You think you're the only one
who realizes Mr. Sarut could be

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:21.240
one of the keys to unlocking the past?

00:18:21.320 --> 00:18:22.680
I've thought of it. But I won't do it.

00:18:23.280 --> 00:18:27.560
Why not?
It's the easiest and most direct way.

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:28.960
Think about it.

00:18:29.040 --> 00:18:32.520
Mr. Sarut used to be
your father's close friend,

00:18:32.600 --> 00:18:35.800
and I've seen him with your mother

00:18:35.880 --> 00:18:37.760
in the past.

00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:41.200
Did you forget what happened the last time

00:18:41.280 --> 00:18:43.560
you went to Mr. Sarut's house?

00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:45.280
You remember yourself that day?

00:18:46.040 --> 00:18:47.520
I just lost it for a moment.

00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:51.040
But after a while, I was fine.

00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:55.120
If it means getting straight answers

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:59.360
without going in circles
chasing Pong and Soi,

00:18:59.440 --> 00:19:00.840
I'm ready to do it.

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:05.480
But I'm not. I won't let
anything happen to you again.

00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:17.520
Has no one ever
spoken nicely to you before?

00:19:22.080 --> 00:19:23.880
Look at your overly happy face.

00:19:25.280 --> 00:19:26.360
Follow me.

00:19:27.480 --> 00:19:30.320
We still have a long list
of things to do today.

00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:33.680
"Long list"? You sound like an old person.

00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:36.400
Hello, Mr. Warat.

00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:40.480
Aunt Nong, guess what good news I have?

00:19:41.200 --> 00:19:43.320
What good news? Just say it.

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:47.080
I'm upset right now. I don't know where
your Uncle Sarut disappeared to again.

00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:49.600
Again?

00:19:49.680 --> 00:19:53.440
I just came back from making offerings
at the storage room shrine,

00:19:53.520 --> 00:19:55.840
and Uncle Sarut was gone.

00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:59.440
Auntie, why do you have to
worship the shrine every single day?

00:20:00.080 --> 00:20:03.040
Forget it. That's my business.

00:20:04.240 --> 00:20:07.600
Hey. Help me find where Uncle Sarut went.

00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:13.160
What if he ran his mouth off to Warat?

00:20:13.240 --> 00:20:17.680
Didn't you say you'd
settled him down? I think…

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:20.720
we need stronger medicine.

00:20:22.480 --> 00:20:23.760
Medicine?

00:20:24.920 --> 00:20:26.760
What nonsense are you talking about?

00:20:27.920 --> 00:20:30.240
I've never given Mr. Sarut anything.

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:41.800
Mr. Rut.

00:21:00.440 --> 00:21:01.760
SARUT

00:21:07.960 --> 00:21:09.040
Thank you.

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:16.640
JIRASIN

00:21:24.080 --> 00:21:28.680
By the way, does Ms. Kluay usually stay
with you like this all the time?

00:21:29.960 --> 00:21:30.920
Yes.

00:21:32.320 --> 00:21:34.320
Kluay helps me with a lot of things.

00:21:36.080 --> 00:21:37.800
You should've told me you were coming.

00:21:38.720 --> 00:21:40.560
I would've gone down
to welcome you myself.

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:44.480
I came today

00:21:45.280 --> 00:21:49.480
because I have something important
I need to talk to you about.

00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:55.640
Then I'll wait outside.

00:21:55.720 --> 00:21:56.840
No need.

00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:59.800
You can say it in front of Kluay.

00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:01.640
I don't keep secrets from her.

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:06.960
It's alright.
I was about to go see Som anyway.

00:22:07.040 --> 00:22:10.560
You two can talk.

00:22:10.640 --> 00:22:12.360
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:20.520
The baby in my womb,

00:22:21.440 --> 00:22:23.320
I won't keep it.

00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:27.000
I'll kill it, and then I'll kill you too!

00:22:33.200 --> 00:22:34.480
Oh, Sin.

00:22:41.360 --> 00:22:44.480
What's the occasion?
You actually came to greet me?

00:22:45.520 --> 00:22:49.640
Yesterday, I heard something happened
at the construction site.

00:22:49.720 --> 00:22:52.520
You're not hurt, are you?

00:22:52.600 --> 00:22:53.880
Are you here to claim credit?

00:22:54.960 --> 00:22:57.960
No. I'm not here to claim anything.

00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:02.640
Good. Because your ridiculous words
didn't mean anything to me.

00:23:02.720 --> 00:23:06.120
You and Warat
could've planned this to fool me.

00:23:08.120 --> 00:23:10.560
You're funny, Sin.

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:14.800
If you're done, leave.
I have something to do.

00:23:14.880 --> 00:23:16.520
Oh, wait.

00:23:17.800 --> 00:23:20.520
There's something else I need to tell you.

00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.080
I saw Ameena today.

00:23:26.440 --> 00:23:30.200
What is wrong with you? I don't want
trouble and you keep bringing it to me.

00:23:32.040 --> 00:23:35.320
I'll deal with you about Ameena myself,
but not today.

00:23:36.720 --> 00:23:37.960
Wait, Sin.

00:23:40.600 --> 00:23:43.760
-What are you going to do to my sister?
-Som.

00:23:45.280 --> 00:23:48.240
I thought Ameena
had already cleared things up with you.

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:50.320
Why are you still bothering my sister?

00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:55.560
What's wrong with you two sisters?

00:23:55.640 --> 00:23:59.480
Open your eyes,
who's the one bothering me?

00:24:00.520 --> 00:24:02.400
You're way too full of yourself.

00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:06.280
Kluay despises you.
She doesn't even want to hear your name.

00:24:07.520 --> 00:24:13.000
Som, I was the one
who came to talk to him.

00:24:14.360 --> 00:24:15.400
Kluay.

00:24:17.520 --> 00:24:21.320
And your shallow plan
to blackmail Ameena into lying to me?

00:24:22.760 --> 00:24:24.160
I'll never believe it.

00:24:26.200 --> 00:24:27.440
Well,

00:24:28.480 --> 00:24:32.320
those two sisters blackmailed me, Sin.

00:24:33.600 --> 00:24:37.160
They forced me to tell you

00:24:39.280 --> 00:24:42.000
that Kluay didn't kill Lakkana.

00:24:42.600 --> 00:24:45.280
Stop talking about Lakkana.
I can't stand it.

00:24:46.040 --> 00:24:47.880
I understand, Sin.

00:24:48.760 --> 00:24:50.920
But can you do me one favor?

00:24:52.360 --> 00:24:54.640
Let me tell them

00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:57.960
that I told you the truth
and you didn't believe me.

00:24:58.600 --> 00:25:01.240
Even if you hadn't asked,
I still wouldn't believe it.

00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:04.840
I heard with my own ears.
Lakkana said Kluay was going to kill her.

00:25:05.440 --> 00:25:06.680
I'll handle this.

00:25:19.760 --> 00:25:21.680
Ameena, you damn snake.

00:25:22.320 --> 00:25:25.840
Ameena followed the plan
you threatened her with. But I

00:25:27.000 --> 00:25:28.640
will never believe anyone
except my sister.

00:25:28.720 --> 00:25:32.280
So this is going to continue, right? Fine.

00:25:32.360 --> 00:25:34.600
We've tried hard enough.

00:25:34.680 --> 00:25:36.800
It's my sister's life.

00:25:36.880 --> 00:25:40.600
It will not be ended
by your stupid little scheme.

00:25:47.880 --> 00:25:49.680
Uncle Rut, what are you doing here?

00:25:57.000 --> 00:26:01.160
I'm warning you for the last time.
Don't show your face at the office again.

00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:05.600
Or I'll tell Warat
what you once were to his mother.

00:26:05.680 --> 00:26:08.000
-Sin.
-I mean it.

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:10.480
Whatever dreams you have
about making him great,

00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:12.600
I'll ruin them completely.

00:26:12.680 --> 00:26:15.040
It's because you're like this, Sin.

00:26:15.120 --> 00:26:18.880
Greedy. Always wanting what isn't yours.

00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:23.040
That's why I secretly
went to see Warat, to protect him.

00:26:23.120 --> 00:26:26.160
-Protect what? Look at yourself.
-Sin!

00:26:26.760 --> 00:26:28.720
I'm trying to knock some sense into you.

00:26:30.360 --> 00:26:33.320
Why? What are you to him?
Why do you have to protect him?

00:26:33.400 --> 00:26:37.360
What right do you have? Tell me.

00:26:38.360 --> 00:26:39.640
Or

00:26:40.400 --> 00:26:43.600
are you afraid
that if I find out the truth,

00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:46.200
I'll ruin everything?

00:26:46.280 --> 00:26:48.440
Don't underestimate me.

00:26:48.520 --> 00:26:51.240
I know more than you think.

00:26:51.320 --> 00:26:54.000
What do you know?

00:26:58.520 --> 00:27:00.160
The very thing you don't want me to know.

00:27:00.240 --> 00:27:01.520
Then tell me.

00:27:03.320 --> 00:27:04.440
What do you know?

00:27:04.520 --> 00:27:07.480
If you tell me what you talked
to him about, I'll tell you.

00:27:23.040 --> 00:27:27.240
If you insist that Kluay be present
for this important matter,

00:27:27.320 --> 00:27:32.160
I have no objection,
even if it's not entirely appropriate.

00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:36.080
Do whatever makes you comfortable.

00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:39.080
All I can do

00:27:39.160 --> 00:27:42.200
is listen and try to understand you.

00:27:43.480 --> 00:27:45.680
And I understand you too, Rat.

00:27:47.880 --> 00:27:49.840
These two files

00:27:49.920 --> 00:27:54.840
are Vanich's latest projects
with a foreign investment group.

00:27:54.920 --> 00:27:56.200
The ones with irregularities?

00:27:59.680 --> 00:28:01.560
Listen to Grandma first.

00:28:01.640 --> 00:28:06.400
It's your duty to review

00:28:06.480 --> 00:28:09.120
the details of the joint venture.

00:28:09.200 --> 00:28:13.240
But that doesn't mean
you must approve it immediately.

00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.800
Just examine it carefully,

00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:18.480
see if anything is missing or flawed,

00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:20.560
then pass it back to Jirasin.

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:26.440
So Jirasin has enough power
to make you come ask me now?

00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:29.440
I'm reaching my limit, Warat.

00:28:30.240 --> 00:28:33.080
No one told me what to say.

00:28:38.440 --> 00:28:41.600
Alright. That's all about work.

00:28:44.800 --> 00:28:50.000
Now I'll talk about
transferring all my Vanich shares to you

00:28:52.120 --> 00:28:54.880
and the new will

00:28:54.960 --> 00:28:58.520
that I prepared,
leaving all my inheritance to you.

00:29:00.080 --> 00:29:01.120
And then what?

00:29:02.160 --> 00:29:03.840
You think that long speech

00:29:04.520 --> 00:29:06.760
will calm me down?

00:29:08.040 --> 00:29:11.200
Why do you always interpret my feelings

00:29:11.800 --> 00:29:14.280
as being about money and assets?

00:29:14.360 --> 00:29:16.840
What I want is my life.

00:29:16.920 --> 00:29:21.360
I want to know who I am,
not these possessions.

00:29:22.240 --> 00:29:23.560
Warat.

00:29:23.640 --> 00:29:25.160
I'll go get him.

00:29:25.240 --> 00:29:26.560
Let him go.

00:29:29.360 --> 00:29:32.920
-Uh, then I'll excuse myself.
-Sit down.

00:29:36.760 --> 00:29:37.840
Yes.

00:29:41.880 --> 00:29:45.800
Rat must be angry
that I never explained about Ampha.

00:29:51.960 --> 00:29:55.520
I think he's more hurt than angry.

00:29:57.160 --> 00:30:01.800
Hurt? But the one who is more hurt
and heartbroken is me.

00:30:05.400 --> 00:30:08.280
I've had to watch the people I love

00:30:08.360 --> 00:30:10.560
suffer again and again.

00:30:11.800 --> 00:30:15.840
I've tried to keep Rat
away from that mess.

00:30:17.920 --> 00:30:23.920
But the more time passes,
the worse it gets.

00:30:28.200 --> 00:30:31.320
Why don't you try letting things

00:30:31.400 --> 00:30:33.760
take their natural course?

00:30:33.840 --> 00:30:37.960
If Rat wants to know about Ms. Ampha,

00:30:38.040 --> 00:30:39.880
let him know.

00:30:39.960 --> 00:30:43.080
No matter the outcome, let him

00:30:43.160 --> 00:30:46.640
take responsibility for his own feelings.
Wouldn't that be better?

00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:52.880
You only talk about what will happen
to Rat. What about me?

00:30:52.960 --> 00:30:56.280
Does that mean
whatever happens to me is fine?

00:30:57.480 --> 00:30:59.760
That's not what I mean.

00:31:01.120 --> 00:31:02.880
It's like dominoes.

00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:10.120
One thing leads to another,

00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:15.640
until it reaches me, reaches Rat,

00:31:16.600 --> 00:31:19.480
and in the end, I might lose him too.

00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:22.960
I can't endure watching terrible things

00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:26.200
happen to me again and again anymore.

00:31:30.920 --> 00:31:32.680
-Grandma…
-Boonsita.

00:31:32.760 --> 00:31:35.320
Can you help me?

00:31:36.200 --> 00:31:37.440
Yes, Grandma.

00:31:38.560 --> 00:31:41.160
Please help me stop everything here.

00:31:41.240 --> 00:31:43.760
From now on, no matter what you see,

00:31:43.840 --> 00:31:46.400
stop everything.

00:31:46.480 --> 00:31:49.840
Don't let Warat see
or know anything ever again.

00:32:00.920 --> 00:32:01.880
Boonsita,

00:32:01.960 --> 00:32:03.880
are you listening to me?

00:32:05.240 --> 00:32:06.280
Grandma.

00:32:16.400 --> 00:32:18.240
Uncle Sarut kept insisting

00:32:18.320 --> 00:32:20.000
that I should be confident

00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:24.360
that I am Vanich's only heir.
Isn't that ridiculous?

00:32:26.040 --> 00:32:27.480
That's strange.

00:32:27.560 --> 00:32:29.360
Oh, but I have something even stranger.

00:32:29.440 --> 00:32:32.960
I found out the name of the company
the maid's brother used to work with Pong.

00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:35.000
What company?

00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:39.000
I think the company name
isn't as interesting

00:32:39.080 --> 00:32:40.880
as the shareholder's name.

00:32:43.640 --> 00:32:47.040
Because the shareholder is Mr. Sarut.

00:32:47.800 --> 00:32:48.760
What?

00:32:49.800 --> 00:32:53.880
Mr. Sarut was the one who sent Pong
to work for Ms. Ampha.

00:32:55.160 --> 00:32:56.320
Is that…

00:32:57.880 --> 00:32:59.480
a coincidence?

00:32:59.560 --> 00:33:03.200
If I spin a quick theory,
it's like Mr. Sarut

00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:06.320
didn't want Ms. Ampha
to rise above Ms. Praewilai.

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:09.640
So he sent Pong and Soi

00:33:09.720 --> 00:33:13.920
to shadow Ms. Ampha
and eliminate her from the Vanich house.

00:33:15.880 --> 00:33:18.360
Mr. Warat, remember this.

00:33:18.960 --> 00:33:23.840
You are Vanich's only heir.
No matter what anyone says,

00:33:23.920 --> 00:33:27.080
don't listen. Stay firm.

00:33:27.160 --> 00:33:30.440
Is it possible that to Uncle Sarut,

00:33:31.280 --> 00:33:34.080
I'm not just the son of his ex-lover?

00:33:34.160 --> 00:33:38.800
Are you saying
you might be Mr. Sarut's son?

00:33:40.120 --> 00:33:41.040
Mr. Warat.

00:33:41.720 --> 00:33:44.920
You've repeated this many times already.

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:47.480
You're grown up now.

00:33:48.520 --> 00:33:49.560
I'll go now.

00:34:08.679 --> 00:34:09.679
Grandma.

00:34:35.239 --> 00:34:36.679
You have another grandchild.

00:34:38.199 --> 00:34:39.239
A granddaughter.

00:34:39.320 --> 00:34:40.560
What are you talking about?

00:34:42.840 --> 00:34:44.719
You once held her hand like this.

00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:48.520
You once looked into her eyes like this.
Think about it, Grandma.

00:34:52.159 --> 00:34:53.520
If I tell you,

00:34:54.760 --> 00:34:57.480
will you stop talking about your visions?

00:34:58.960 --> 00:35:02.560
Yes. I promise.

00:35:03.160 --> 00:35:06.680
I have only one grandchild,
which is Warat.

00:35:08.040 --> 00:35:10.720
That's not true. You're lying.

00:35:11.320 --> 00:35:13.360
Whether it's true or not,

00:35:13.440 --> 00:35:16.120
you have no right
to be rude to me like that.

00:35:16.200 --> 00:35:18.640
I'm not being rude.

00:35:18.720 --> 00:35:21.280
I just wonder why you won't tell Warat.

00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:24.240
You don't want him to be hurt,

00:35:24.320 --> 00:35:26.800
but you're the one hurting him.

00:35:26.880 --> 00:35:28.720
Stop it right now, Boonsita.

00:35:29.520 --> 00:35:33.240
Let Warat learn the truth about himself.

00:35:37.920 --> 00:35:40.120
Boonsita, what's gotten into you?

00:35:44.880 --> 00:35:47.000
Would you like more dessert, ma'am?

00:35:48.360 --> 00:35:49.600
No.

00:36:02.240 --> 00:36:03.480
Why are you calling?

00:36:05.040 --> 00:36:07.840
Because I know
someone wants to talk to me.

00:36:10.680 --> 00:36:12.480
I fought with Grandma again.

00:36:12.560 --> 00:36:15.440
In the end, she used the same old method.

00:36:15.520 --> 00:36:17.880
Oh. But she did

00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:20.760
transfer the majority shares
of Vanich to me.

00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:23.360
I wish I could bear…

00:36:24.680 --> 00:36:26.400
the Vanich surname.

00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:28.360
I will never accept it

00:36:29.480 --> 00:36:32.960
while my family's past
is still this murky.

00:36:34.480 --> 00:36:37.560
I understand. Still, what a pity.

00:36:40.240 --> 00:36:41.320
I won't wait anymore.

00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:42.640
What do you mean?

00:36:42.720 --> 00:36:44.920
Since I know

00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:49.560
where the best source of information is,
I'm going there right now.

00:36:49.640 --> 00:36:50.560
Mr. Warat.

00:36:50.640 --> 00:36:51.600
I gotta go.

00:36:56.360 --> 00:36:57.920
Hey, Kluay.

00:36:58.640 --> 00:36:59.920
What's wrong?

00:37:01.160 --> 00:37:04.480
Hey. Did Grandma do this to you?

00:37:04.560 --> 00:37:07.880
No. It's not because of your grandma.

00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:10.160
Unbelievable. Both grandma and grandson.

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:12.120
Why are you sitting here?

00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:16.360
Did you see something that drained you?
Right? I completely forgot about that.

00:37:17.080 --> 00:37:19.400
Yes. I saw a lot.

00:37:19.480 --> 00:37:22.200
But don't question me yet.

00:37:22.280 --> 00:37:25.640
I won't tell you
until I'm sure what it is.

00:37:25.720 --> 00:37:28.520
-A ghost or a person?
-I just said I wouldn't tell.

00:37:28.600 --> 00:37:30.680
-A man or a woman?
-Ugh, Mr. Warat.

00:37:30.760 --> 00:37:32.960
Okay, okay. I won't ask.

00:37:33.040 --> 00:37:35.320
So are we just going to sit and talk here?

00:37:37.320 --> 00:37:39.320
I'm fine now.

00:37:40.560 --> 00:37:41.640
Come.

00:37:41.720 --> 00:37:43.400
-You okay?
-I'm fine. I can stand up now.

00:37:44.880 --> 00:37:48.240
Alright. Then go somewhere with me.

00:37:48.320 --> 00:37:49.400
No.

00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:52.200
I haven't even said where,
and you're already refusing?

00:37:53.040 --> 00:37:54.760
I'm not falling for your trick again.

00:37:54.840 --> 00:37:57.560
Last time,
you dragged me to Ameena's house.

00:37:58.280 --> 00:38:00.040
But this time, it's really important.

00:38:00.120 --> 00:38:02.880
I promise I won't take you
anywhere you don't want to go.

00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:05.760
Are you sure?

00:38:05.840 --> 00:38:07.280
I'm sure.

00:38:07.360 --> 00:38:08.760
Only somewhere you like.

00:38:10.080 --> 00:38:12.640
Listen to you.
I might not go with you at all.

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:15.680
Hey, are you okay?

00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:17.120
I'm fine.

00:38:23.240 --> 00:38:25.840
If we were really dating, that'd be nice.

00:38:26.640 --> 00:38:27.640
Yeah.

00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:30.560
NEXT EPISODE

00:38:33.320 --> 00:38:34.560
Is this the donor's name?

00:38:34.640 --> 00:38:37.400
Yes. Ms. Anong.

00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:42.640
Are you sure Kluay is just an orphan

00:38:42.720 --> 00:38:45.080
that the orphanage owner took in?

00:38:45.160 --> 00:38:49.760
I'll have to teach you two a lesson.

00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:52.880
Go ahead.

00:41:16.080 --> 00:41:18.080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon